; iq2xxs-msl.fk — GGUF type 16 (IQ2_XXS) as a Metal kernel the BODY emits, so the QUANTIZED bytes are
; what lives on the GPU and the 2-bit unpack happens THERE.
;
; WHY THIS EXISTS. iq2xxs-dequant.fk (Stone 24) proved the 66-byte / 256-element IQ2_XXS superblock on
; the CPU arithmetic floor — bit-exact vs an independent from-spec oracle over 61 952 real DeepSeek
; weights. But IQ2_XXS is 42.6% of the file's bytes and the expert weights of 31 of 43 layers; a CPU
; carver cannot fold a MoE. This cell turns "can read" into "can run": the quantized block bytes go to
; the device unchanged and the decode happens on the GPU. It is the last dequant type still CPU-only, and
; DeepSeek's ffn_down_exps are exactly type 16, so the MoE fold needs them here.
;
; THE ONE NEW THING versus mxfp4-msl.fk / q6k-msl.fk: two `constant` ARRAY LITERALS. MXFP4's whole
; codebook is arithmetic (E2M1 is a formula); IQ2's is a TRAINED table with no closed form — 256 curated
; eight-tuples of {8,25,43} and a 128-entry sign table where the 8th sign of each octet is BORN as the
; parity of the other seven (corpus row 855, paritylock). Both tables are carried verbatim. This file
; emits them as `constant uchar iq2_grid[2048]` and `constant uchar iq2_ksigns[128]`, built by iq2m-join
; from the SAME (iq2-grid) / (iq2-ksigns) lists the CPU carver uses — so the device table is byte-
; identical to the carver's BY CONSTRUCTION, not by a second transcription that could drift. GPU_GAPS
; flagged emitting a `constant` array literal as historically untried; it is pure str_concat over
; int_to_str, and mx-msl-band's shape proves the text before any GPU runs.
;
; BIT-EXACTNESS IS THE BAR, not a derived bound, and by the carver's own §3 argument: w is an EXACT
; product of an f16-derived d, 0.125 (dyadic), a small odd int (<= 31) and a magnitude (<= 43) — <= 21
; significand bits, bit-identical in f32 and f64. There is no accumulation and no float scale surprise
; beyond the one f16 d. So Form's answer and the GPU's f32 answer are the same real number and the same
; f32; the gate is equality with no epsilon, exactly as the MX carvers hit.
;
; PARITYLOCK, ON THE DEVICE. The 8th sign is not stored; it is the parity of the other seven, and ksigns
; is where it is born. This kernel does NOT re-derive the unpack: it feeds sign_idx straight through the
; transcribed iq2_ksigns table, so the parity bit rides along in the table's 8th bit. A kernel that
; "simplified" the table away would be right seven values in eight and silently wrong on the last, per
; group of eight — the exact silent-partial shape this body has been burned by. The table is the DoF.
;
; NO HEADER, ON PURPOSE — the q6k-msl / mxfp4-msl discipline. This file emits no `#include <metal_stdlib>`
; and no `using namespace metal;`: the f16 super-scale d is decoded by ARITHMETIC (iq2_f16 is fd-value at
; eb=5, mb=10 transcribed, exactly q6k_f16's shape), not by `as_type<half>`. There is no library call at
; all in the dequant kernel. The header, if a unit needs one, is emitted ONCE by the assembling cell
; (qml-msl-header), never restated here — a second `using namespace metal;` makes this body's `round`
; ambiguous and the unit stops compiling.
;
; EVERY BIT-OP IS AN ARITHMETIC IDENTITY, so the emitted C matches the carver's div/mod form line for
; line and the Form-side mirror (iq2m-flat-at) can be checked against the carver with no bitwise operator
; anywhere: x >> s = div x 2^s ; x & (2^k-1) = mod x 2^k ; x & (1<<j)? = mod (div x 2^j) 2. The one place
; a device would naturally reach for `>>`/`&` (aux1's 7-bit sign fields) is written as div/mod so the
; mirror is a faithful hand-copy, not a paraphrase.
;
; RADIUS (`aporon`). This cell emits the DEQUANT kernel and its Form mirror only. A FUSED matvec-over-IQ2
; (dequant inside the dot, like mxfp4-msl's slot path) is what the MoE fold ultimately needs; whether it
; is reachable on IQ2's block geometry is noted in the receipt, not built here. The GEOMETRY it decodes
; is gguf-manifest.fk's `gm-blk n 256 66`, proven by that file's own offset chain; a GPU agreeing with
; the CPU carver proves the TRANSCRIPTION and the residency, and the carver already carries bit-exactness
; vs an independent oracle — so this closes IQ2 on the device to the same class MX reached.
;
; Kin: iq2xxs-dequant.fk (iq2-* — the CPU carver this must equal, and the ONE true (iq2-grid)/(iq2-ksigns)
; both sides share), mxfp4-msl.fk (the emit idiom, the read-back-into-Form discipline, the no-header rule),
; q6k-msl.fk (q6k_f16 — the f16-by-arithmetic this transcribes), f16-decode.fk (fd-value at (5,10)),
; qk-matvec-lane.fk (qml-msl-header — the body's one metal_stdlib).
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/format-arith.fk form-stdlib/f16-decode.fk form-stdlib/iq2xxs-dequant.fk
;
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/iq2xxs-msl-band.fk (the transcription, against the carver, on the real
;            blocks) and form/native/metal/metal_iq2_gpu.sh (the GPU, Mac-only, head AND distant block).

(do
    ; ================= the transcription, read back into Form =================
    ; Everything here is what the emitted C computes, written in Form with the same integer identities and
    ; the same offsets, so iq2xxs-msl-band.fk can falsify the TEXT against iq2xxs-dequant's independently
    ; written carver rather than against a paraphrase of it. It reads a byte LIST via nth, exactly as the
    ; carver does, so the two readings are comparable element by element; the f16 decode here is OPEN-CODED
    ; (the C's iq2_f16) while the carver routes d through fd-f16 — that is the independence on the d path.

    (defn iq2m-mod (a n) (sub a (mul (div a n) n)))
    ; 2^k as an exact int, k >= 0 (the aux1 sign shift 0/7/14/21 and the sign bit 0..7)
    (defn iq2m-upow2 (k) (if (eq k 0) 1 (mul 2 (iq2m-upow2 (sub k 1)))))
    ; 2^e as a float, e signed (the f16 exponent, ex-15 in -15..16, plus the -14 subnormal step)
    (defn iq2m-p2f (e)
        (if (lt e 0) (mul 0.5 (iq2m-p2f (add e 1)))
            (if (gt e 0) (mul 2.0 (iq2m-p2f (sub e 1))) 1.0)))

    ; --- f16 decode by arithmetic: fd-value at (eb 5, mb 10), bias 15 — the C's iq2_f16, line for line.
    (defn iq2m-f16 (bits)
        (do
            (let mant (iq2m-mod bits 1024))
            (let ex   (iq2m-mod (div bits 1024) 32))
            (let sgn  (div bits 32768))
            (let frac (div (mul 1.0 mant) 1024.0))
            (let mag (if (eq ex 0)
                         (mul (iq2m-p2f (sub 0 14)) frac)
                         (mul (iq2m-p2f (sub ex 15)) (add 1.0 frac))))
            (if (eq sgn 1) (sub 0.0 mag) mag)))

    ; --- one weight at FLAT element index idx, block-0 byte base `base` in the byte list. Mirrors iq2_w:
    ; blk = idx/256, within = idx%256, block byte base = base + 66*blk. Same field offsets as the carver.
    (defn iq2m-flat-at (bytes base idx)
        (do
            (let blk (div idx 256))
            (let within (sub idx (mul blk 256)))
            (let off (add base (mul 66 blk)))
            (let hbits (add (nth bytes off) (mul 256 (nth bytes (add off 1)))))
            (let d (iq2m-f16 hbits))
            (let ib32 (div within 32))
            (let rem (iq2m-mod within 32))
            (let l (div rem 8))
            (let j (iq2m-mod rem 8))
            (let gbase (add off (add 2 (mul 8 ib32))))
            (let gidx (nth bytes (add gbase l)))
            (let aux1 (add (nth bytes (add gbase 4))
                      (add (mul 256      (nth bytes (add gbase 5)))
                      (add (mul 65536    (nth bytes (add gbase 6)))
                           (mul 16777216 (nth bytes (add gbase 7)))))))
            (let scalecode (div (nth bytes (add gbase 7)) 16))
            (let scale (mul (mul 0.125 d) (add (mul 2 scalecode) 1)))
            (let signidx (iq2m-mod (div aux1 (iq2m-upow2 (mul 7 l))) 128))
            (let signs (nth (iq2-ksigns) signidx))
            (let sbit (iq2m-mod (div signs (iq2m-upow2 j)) 2))
            (let sgn (if (eq sbit 1) -1 1))
            (let mag (nth (iq2-grid) (add (mul gidx 8) j)))
            (mul (mul scale sgn) mag)))

    ; ================= the constant array literals =================
    ; join a list of ints into "a,b,c" — the head-wise fold, O(n), so a 2048-entry table builds without an
    ; O(n^2) nth walk. Built from the SAME lists the carver decodes: the device grid IS the carver's grid.
    (defn iq2m-join-tail (xs) (if (nil? xs) "" (str_concat "," (str_concat (int_to_str (head xs)) (iq2m-join-tail (tail xs))))))
    (defn iq2m-join (xs) (if (nil? xs) "" (str_concat (int_to_str (head xs)) (iq2m-join-tail (tail xs)))))

    (defn iq2m-msl-grid ()
        (str_concat "constant uchar iq2_grid[2048] = { " (str_concat (iq2m-join (iq2-grid)) " };\n")))
    (defn iq2m-msl-ksigns ()
        (str_concat "constant uchar iq2_ksigns[128] = { " (str_concat (iq2m-join (iq2-ksigns)) " };\n")))

    ; ================= the emitted MSL =================
    ; One fragment per meaning, composed by str_concat, so a diff of the emitted text points at a recipe.

    ; --- the spine: integer mod, integer 2^k, float 2^e, and f16-by-arithmetic (fd-value at (5,10)). No
    ; library call, no header. iq2_f16 is q6k_f16's shape; iq2_upow2 is the exact power of two the sign
    ; shifts need; iq2_pow2 is the signed float power the f16 exponent needs. ---
    (defn iq2m-msl-spine ()
        "static inline int iq2_mod(int a, int n) { return a - (a / n) * n; } static inline uint iq2_upow2(uint k) { uint a = 1u; for (uint i = 0u; i < k; ++i) a = a * 2u; return a; } static inline float iq2_pow2(int e) { float a = 1.0f; int k = 0; if (e >= 0) { while (k < e) { a = a * 2.0f; k = k + 1; } } else { while (k < -e) { a = a * 0.5f; k = k + 1; } } return a; } static inline float iq2_f16(int bits) { int mant = iq2_mod(bits, 1024); int ex = iq2_mod(bits / 1024, 32); int sgn = bits / 32768; float frac = float(mant) / 1024.0f; float mag = (ex == 0) ? iq2_pow2(-14) * frac : iq2_pow2(ex - 15) * (1.0f + frac); return (sgn == 1) ? -mag : mag; } ")

    ; --- one weight at a flat element index, iq2m-flat-at in C. qb points at the block-0 byte base (the
    ; carrier binds that with a buffer offset, so no 32-bit file offset is ever formed for a 60 GB file).
    ; The 7-bit sign fields of aux1 are read by div/mod, NOT `>>`/`&`, so this is the mirror's twin. ---
    (defn iq2m-msl-weight ()
        "static inline float iq2_w(device const uchar* qb, uint idx) { uint blk = idx / 256u; uint within = idx - blk * 256u; uint off = blk * 66u; int hbits = int(qb[off]) + 256 * int(qb[off + 1u]); float d = iq2_f16(hbits); uint ib32 = within / 32u; uint rem = within - ib32 * 32u; uint l = rem / 8u; uint j = rem - l * 8u; uint gbase = off + 2u + 8u * ib32; int gidx = int(qb[gbase + l]); uint aux1 = uint(qb[gbase + 4u]) + 256u * uint(qb[gbase + 5u]) + 65536u * uint(qb[gbase + 6u]) + 16777216u * uint(qb[gbase + 7u]); int scalecode = int(qb[gbase + 7u]) / 16; float scale = 0.125f * d * float(2 * scalecode + 1); uint signidx = (aux1 / iq2_upow2(7u * l)) % 128u; int signs = int(iq2_ksigns[signidx]); int sbit = iq2_mod(signs / int(iq2_upow2(j)), 2); float sgn = (sbit == 1) ? -1.0f : 1.0f; int mag = int(iq2_grid[uint(gidx) * 8u + j]); return (scale * sgn) * float(mag); } ")

    ; the two tables plus the spine plus the weight fn — everything the dequant kernel needs, once.
    (defn iq2m-msl-helpers ()
        (str_concat (iq2m-msl-grid)
        (str_concat (iq2m-msl-ksigns)
        (str_concat (iq2m-msl-spine) (iq2m-msl-weight)))))

    ; --- the kernel: dequant a range into f32, one thread per weight. `off` is a flat ELEMENT offset, so a
    ; caller can dequant a tile anywhere in a slice without moving the resident bytes — the aporon
    ; discipline, made reachable. `qb` is bound at the block-0 byte base by the carrier. ---
    (defn iq2m-dequant-body (fname)
        (str_concat "kernel void "
        (str_concat fname
            " (device const uchar* qb [[buffer(0)]], device float* w [[buffer(1)]], constant uint& off [[buffer(2)]], constant uint& cnt [[buffer(3)]], uint i [[thread_position_in_grid]]) { if (i >= cnt) return; w[i] = iq2_w(qb, off + i); }")))

    ; each kernel self-contained (tables + spine + body); a unit that also needs a header reaches for
    ; qml-msl-header in the assembling cell, exactly once.
    (defn iq2m-dequant-msl (fname) (str_concat (iq2m-msl-helpers) (iq2m-dequant-body fname)))

    0)
